<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>CBRWS V1 Greeting Relation</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
</head>
<body>
<header>
  <h1>CBRWS Relation: <code>cbrws:greeting</code></h1>
  <p>
    This document describes the custom <code>cbrws:greeting</code>
    relation used by the CBRWS v1 API.
  </p>
</header>

<main>
  <section>
    <h2>Meaning</h2>
    <p>
      The <code>cbrws:greeting</code> relation identifies a resource
      that returns the API's greeting representation.
    </p>
    <p>
      Relation document URL: <code>{{ relation_url }}</code><br />
      Target resource URL: <code>{{ resource_url }}</code>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Target Resource</h2>
    <p>
      Dereferencing this relation reaches <code>{{ resource_url }}</code>.
      That resource supports <code>GET</code>, <code>HEAD</code>, and
      <code>OPTIONS</code>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Successful responses use
      <code>{{ resource_media_type }}</code> and conform to the profile
      <code>{{ profile_url }}</code>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Representation Contract</h2>
    <p>The <code>/api/greeting</code> resource returns a JSON object with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>message</code>: a greeting string</li>
      <li><code>_links.self</code>: a link to the greeting resource</li>
      <li><code>_links.up</code>: a link back to <code>/api</code></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Content Negotiation</h2>
    <p>This relation document supports:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>text/html</code> for this documentation page</li>
      <li><code>application/schema+json</code> for a JSON Schema of the target resource</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</main>
</body>
</html>
